The remaining work is on the API/controller side.

Can we close as duplicate of https://github.com/openwhisk/openwhisk/issues/465?

Proposed fix in #1665.
That was the intent - the test missed it because it invokes an action in the same namespace as the subject namespace. Will need to adjust the test to invoke an action in a package.

@csantanapr want to write the test turning your example above into a test and send a pull request against my branch?

I agree that the prefix "An error has occurred:" is not at all desirable and should almost definitely be removed for NLS reasons among others but also because it limits the return type to a string. It could definitely be valuable to have a structure returned.

I would tend to not treat Promise.reject("oh no!") and Promise.reject(new Error("oh no!) identically and would suggest special casing Error Objects and converting them to a regular object with just a "name" and "message". Like so...

```
{
  "error": {
    "name":"Error",
    "message":"oh no!"
  }
}
```
It's tempting to also expose the enumerable properties of the Error but I would be cautious here. JavaScript Errors in my experience can contain references to Native elements as well as internal details you would not normally want to share and can also throw exceptions during a subsequent call to JSON.stringify. It can be done -- just prepare to write some pretty defensive code here.

Instead, If someone really really wants to pass stacks etc. I would suggest they create and reject with their own custom regular Object.
